.:: Puzzle 4x4-Level-8-4::.
There 4 different types of food: apple, banana, cucumber, plum
The people grow 4 different varities of flowers: iris, marigold, daffodil, azalea
The people use 4 different means of transport: roller, boat, motorbike, trike
4 different pets are kept: horse, hamster, dog, frog
 1. the person who growsdaffodil is not the person driving the roller##6
 2. the person driving the trike is on the left or right of the owner of the dog##3
 3. the person eating plum is the person driving the motorbike##1
 4. the person eating banana is between the person driving the roller and the person driving the boat##2
 5. the person who growsdaffodil is on the left or right of the owner of the horse##3
 6. the owner of the horse is not to the right of the person eating banana##8
 7. the person who growsazalea is in an odd position##4
 8. the person who growsdaffodil is somewhere to the right of the person who growsiris##5
 9. the person who growsazalea is on the right of the person driving the trike##1
10. the person driving the boat is the owner of the horse##1
11. the owner of the hamster is not to the right of the person eating apple##8
12. the person driving the roller is on the left or right of the owner of the hamster##3
13. the person who growsdaffodil is on the right of the person who growsiris##1
14. the person driving the boat is on the left or right of the owner of the hamster##3
15. the person who growsiris is in an odd position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|         |      1      |         2          |    3    |    4     |
| Food    | cucumber    | banana             | apple   | plum     |
| Flower   | iris | daffodil            | azalea | marigold    |
| Transport     | boat | trike | roller  | motorbike |
| Pet   | horse  | hamster               | dog  | frog   |

